<p>New and revised entries at online philosophy resources, new reviews of philosophy books, new podcast episodes, and more—including, now, a section on recently published open access philosophy books (if you tell us about them).<span id="more-55878"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-44641 aligncenter wp-dark-mode-bg-image" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/weekly-update-logo-2023.png" sizes="auto, (max-width: 606px) 100vw, 606px" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/weekly-update-logo-2023.png 2139w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/weekly-update-logo-2023-300x173.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/weekly-update-logo-2023-1024x592.png 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/weekly-update-logo-2023-768x444.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/weekly-update-logo-2023-1536x888.png 1536w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/weekly-update-logo-2023-2048x1183.png 2048w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/weekly-update-logo-2023-400x231.png 400w" alt="" width="589" height="340" /></p>
<p>This update covers the past two weeks.</p>
<p class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image">(If we missed anything, please let us know.)</p>
<h3><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/index.html">SEP</a></h3>
<p><em>New</em>:</p>
<ol>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/albert-great/">Albert the Great</a> by Bruno Tremblay.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/francis-bacon/">Francis Bacon</a> by Markku Peltonen.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/aristotle-de-motu/">Aristotle’s De Motu Animalium</a> by Klaus Corcilius.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/justep-intext/">Internalist vs. Externalist Conceptions of Epistemic Justification</a> by Clayton Littlejohn.</li>
</ol>
<p><em>Revised</em>:</p>
<ol>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/arrows-theorem/">Arrow’s Theorem</a> by Michael Morreau.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/global-democracy/">Global Democracy</a> by Jonathan Kuyper.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/ibn-arabi/">Ibn ‘Arabī</a> by William Chittick.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/states-of-affairs/">States of Affairs</a> by Mark Textor.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/time/">Time</a> by Nina Emery, Ned Markosian, and Meghan Sullivan.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/anarchism/">Anarchism</a> by Andrew Fiala.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/analogy-medieval/">Medieval Theories of Analogy</a> by E. Jennifer Ashworth and Domenic D’Ettore.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/settheory-early/">The Early Development of Set Theory</a> by José Ferreirós.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/arabic-islamic-influence/">Influence of Arabic and Islamic Philosophy on the Latin West</a> by Dag Nikolaus Hasse.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/depiction/">Depiction</a> by John Hyman and Katerina Bantinaki.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/aesthetics-of-everyday/">Aesthetics of the Everyday</a> by Yuriko Saito.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/feminism-femhist/">Feminist History of Philosophy</a> by Charlotte Witt, Lisa Shapiro, Christina Van Dyke, Lydia L. Moland, and Marcia Robinson.</li>
<li><a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/properties/">Properties</a> by Francesco Orilia and Michele Paolini Paoletti.</li>
</ol>
